name: Warung Titiran
address: R4X4+4WX, Jl. Jelantik Gingsir, Sukasada, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia
review 1: Great family owned Warung with very delicious food! I can highly recommend stopping here when passing by!
review 2:
Delicious food prepared in a reasonable time. Seemed authentic, although I am no authority on this. Service was very friendly (gave us complimentary bananas grown next to the restaurant + crackers).

Reasonable price (slightly more than a cheaper warung). Nice seating. Recommend for both vegetarian and normal diets.

Side note. - no food poisoning for fellow white ppl. Did not serve beer.
review 3: We are a couple from Spain and we really liked the place. We loved the service and the food was amazing. Good price, good people and good place. I would recommend it 100%.
review 4: A lovely little Restaurant with very friendly owners. I really enjoy come back here again to watch a nice Sunset
review 5: I did not find this place on google, we just randomly stopped by. Yes there are no pictures and stuff but this is a really good restaurant. The food was the best Indonesian food we had‚Ä¶ and we had a lot. We only eat vegetarian and we had good options. The staff was ofc so nice and we loved it here. I did not take photos, but if you are here please do and put them in your review to help them grow. Definitely worth a visit!!
